7.1.1 - W11SR06: Insufficient Cloud SaaS Backup and Restoration Capability
ISM controls:
•	1511; 1514 (Relating to the backup of important data and software to ensure business continuity).
•	1515; 1516 (Relating to the regular testing of backup restoration processes).
•	1703 (Relating to the development and maintenance of business continuity and disaster recovery plans).
Current Risk
There is a risk that an insufficient or ineffective Microsoft cloud SaaS backup solution—including inadequate restoration controls, processes, and tools—will significantly reduce the agency's business continuity objectives. Specifically, failure to meet Recovery Time Objectives (RTO) and Recovery Point Objectives (RPO) for the Windows 11 management solution could lead to prolonged operational downtime and data loss following a cloud-side incident or accidental deletion.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
LIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	HIGH
Recommendations:
•	Implement a Third-Party SaaS Backup Solution: Deploy a dedicated backup platform (e.g., Veeam, Commvault, or Druva) that provides independent, off-site protection for M365 and Intune configuration data, separate from the primary Microsoft tenant.
•	Formalise RTO and RPO Requirements: Define and document clear business continuity requirements specifically for the endpoint management plane to ensure restoration capabilities align with agency operational needs.
•	Regular Restoration Drills: Establish a schedule for periodic restoration testing of critical tenant configurations and user data to validate the integrity of backups and the effectiveness of recovery procedures.
- Treatment #1
•	Configure automated daily backups of Intune policies, Entra ID objects, and SharePoint/OneDrive data with a minimum retention period of 12 months.
•	Integrate backup status reporting into the departmental security operations dashboard to ensure immediate visibility of any backup failures.
•	Develop a detailed "Cloud Recovery Playbook" that outlines step-by-step procedures for restoring the Windows 11 management environment in the event of a catastrophic tenant failure.
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
The deployment of an independent backup solution and formalised recovery processes ensures that the agency is not solely reliant on Microsoft’s native "deleted item" retention. By validating recovery workflows through regular testing, the likelihood of failing to meet continuity objectives is reduced to "Unlikely." While the moderate consequence remains due to the inherent disruption of any restoration event, the overall risk is significantly mitigated.
